<br>
A rotation will not work for 2 reasons:<br>
<br>
1)  Shissar Spirit spawning is a &quot;reward&quot; for killin Cazic Thule.  The guild/group that kills CT should be able to reap the reward for that kill.<br>
<br>
2)  More importantly, the reason that the Ragefire rotation works is that the server as a whole benefits from clerics with their epic.  If I were a cleric with an epic, I would feel an obligation (maybe not the best word...) to use it for the server's benefit.  The enchanter epic does not benefit the server.  A GUILD may feel that it benefits them, and they will do whatever it takes to assure some of their enchanters have the epic, but it doesn't benefit the server in the least.<br>
<br>
Serius, Enchanter to King Tearis Thex<br>
Tanking Bixie Drones for 54 Levels<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utyzman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyzman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Werewolf</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 12:13:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shissar Spirit Sightings</span><hr size=1> First of all, Shissar is no longer triggered by killing CT... he is on a spawn timer.  This was changed months ago... unless they changed it again in the last patch.<br>
<br>
Secondly, the Ragefire rotation works because it's easier for everyone then FFA... and far more civil.  Everyone agrees to abide by the rotation because it would require FAR more effort to fight it.  I've read about the viscious FG training, powerlooting, etc that happens on other servers... I'm glad that's not an issue here.<br>
<br>
Third, the Cleric epic benefits the server as a whole... but very little.  It really benefits server RAIDS more then anything else, other then that it's just a benefit to the individual and the guild they are in.<br>
<br>
A rotation for the Shissar would be nice in theory, but very hard to do.  Setting the initial order is hard enough... but determining who has to clear the plane and how that affects the calendar are other big issues as well.<br>
<br>
